0":"circa 1420","after 1431":"na 1431","1416":"1416","Gillingham, Kent, England":"Gillingham, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Chislehurst, Kent, England":"Chislehurst, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","London, England":"London, England","Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England":"Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England"},"en":{"1398–1445":"1398–1445","1395–1456":"1395–1456","1416–1468":"1416–1468","1420–1465":"1420–1465","1372–1397":"1372–1397","1375–1431":"1375–1431","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1372":"1372","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1445":"1445","1456":"1456","1465":"1465","1398":"1398","1431":"1431","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1397":"1397","about 1420":"about 1420","after 1431":"after 1431","1416":"1416","Gillingham, Kent, England":"Gillingham, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Chislehurst, Kent, England":"Chislehurst, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","London, England":"London, England","Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England":"Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bamme","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Dutch: habitational name from any of the many places in the Netherlands named Dam or Ten Damme, from <i>dam</i> ‘dam, dike’.","North German: habitational name from any of the places called Damm and Damme in Oldenburg, Rhineland, Brandenburg, and Pomerania."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Bamme was born in 1398, in Gillingham, Kent, England, her father, Adam Bamme Mayor of London, was 27 and her mother, Margaret Stodeye, was 23. She married Thomas Walsingham in 1415, in Gillingham, Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1445, in London, England, at the age of 47, and was buried in Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England."},"et":{"1398–1445":"1398–1445","1395–1456":"1395–1456","1416–1468":"1416–1468","1420–1465":"1420–1465","1372–1397":"1372–1397","1375–1431":"1375–1431","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1372":"1372","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1445":"1445","1456":"1456","1465":"1465","1398":"1398","1431":"1431","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1397":"1397","about 1420":"umbes 1420","after 1431":"pärast 1431","1416":"1416","Gillingham, Kent, England":"Gillingham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chislehurst, Kent, England":"Chislehurst, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","London, England":"London, England","Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England":"Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England"},"fi":{"1398–1445":"1398–1445","1395–1456":"1395–1456","1416–1468":"1416–1468","1420–1465":"1420–1465","1372–1397":"1372–1397","1375–1431":"1375–1431","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1372":"1372","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1445":"1445","1456":"1456","1465":"1465","1398":"1398","1431":"1431","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1397":"1397","about 1420":"noin 1420","after 1431":"1431 jälkeen","1416":"1416","Gillingham, Kent, England":"Gillingham, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Chislehurst, Kent, England":"Chislehurst, Kent, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","London, England":"London, England","Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England":"Precinct of St Katherine, Middlesex, England"},"fr":{"1398–1445":"1398–1445","1395–1456":"1395–1456","1416–1468":"1416–1468","1420–1465":"1420–1465","1372–1397":"1372–1397","1375–1431":"1375–1431","1396":"1396","1395":"1395","1372":"1372","1415":"1415","1468":"1468","1445":"1445","1456":"1456","1465":"1465","1398":"1398","1431":"1431","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1397":"1397","about 1420":"environ 1420","after 1431":"après 1431","1416":"1416","Gillingham,